HEADWORD: Crossruff
<hw>Cross"ruff`</hw> <pr>(-r?f`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Whist)</fld>
<def>The play in bridge or whist where partners trump each a different
suit, and lead to each other for that purpose; -- called also
<altname>seesaw</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

